        "text": "2026-03-18 Think have a decent sense on how to model #s but still have some difficulty pinning down what large wins to model and how they contribute to P&L. ESS GPM at 38% in 2025 and likely goes to 33-34% in 2026 with what we know. Expert calls suggest that the upside is in penetration and the downside is in hours deployed. End demand is also much more diversified than I initially thought, of the 20GWh y/y growth for Sungrow perhaps only single digit is from US with the rest from MENA, Europe, LATAM and such. \n\nEnd up at roughly single digit below cons and narrower gap with cons in 27 which brings us to 16x. I think funding long more than alpha long per se.",
